Frost (Albertson's brand) and Svedka are 5x distilled. TL;DR: 1) Don't spontaneously buy a pet  2) do your research because pet store staff members aren't really experts who know everything about every animal  and 3) don't buy animals from chains (ex. PetSmart/Petco) because they use breeding mills.  I know that this video is pretty old  but for anyone who sees this: please don't spontaneously buy an animal  especially not from PetSmart  Petco  or any other chain pet store. The pet store staff are NOT EXPERTS on every animal that is sold in their stores  so they will often wind up unintentionally providing you with false information.  Pets are not something to be purchased randomly without doing any prior research. For example  bearded dragons (which are sold at both PetSmart and Petco) are often thought to live on sand in the wild (yes  there is some sand  but there is not only sand; it's not the only option that they have). This means that staff at pet stores will tell you to use sand as a substrate  which can cause impaction and eventually kill your new reptile. My point is: do your research beforehand. Don't only rely on what inexperienced (NOT ACTUAL PROFESSIONALS) pet store staff members know about caring for your new pet.  Additionally  stores like PetSmart and Petco use breeding mills to supply their small animals (rodents  reptiles  birds  etc). That's a whole other issue that I won't talk about here  but you can easily google to find more information (spoiler alert: it's horrifying).
